# Alfred Concierge — environment variables for analytics + search verification.
# Copy to .env.local for local dev, or set in the Vercel project's Environment
# Variables panel for production. Vite only exposes vars prefixed VITE_.

# ── Search Console verification ──────────────────────────────────────
# Substituted into <meta name="google-site-verification"> in index.html.
# Get from https://search.google.com/search-console — pick the HTML tag
# verification method, copy the value of the `content` attribute.
VITE_GSC_VERIFICATION=

# Substituted into <meta name="msvalidate.01"> in index.html. Bing now also
# powers ChatGPT search, so set this even if you mostly care about Google.
# Get from https://www.bing.com/webmasters
VITE_BING_VERIFICATION=

# ── Analytics ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Google Analytics 4 measurement ID, format "G-XXXXXXXXXX".
# Get from https://analytics.google.com — Admin → Property → Data streams.
# Vercel Analytics + Speed Insights run alongside this and need no IDs.
VITE_GA4_ID=

# Microsoft Clarity project ID (free heatmaps + session replays).
# Get from https://clarity.microsoft.com — create a project, copy the ID
# from the install snippet (between the quotes after the last comma).
VITE_CLARITY_ID=
